					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>316 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>190</height>
										<width>140</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>145</height>
										<width>105</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>316 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 10 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Much damaged. Some leaves stuck on modern paper.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="14" writtenLines="14">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Visible mastara ruling.</p>
									<p>Chapter numbers given in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso, only partly preserved.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Oriental semi-cursive script of the 16th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Daniel ben Mosheh ben Yeshayah Firuz</name>: inscribed, folio 198v of volume 2.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major">
								<p>
									<locus from="1r" to="18v"/>, <locus from="119r" to="134v"/>, <locus from="313r" to="313v"/>: supplied by a later hand, of approximately the end of 17th century or the beginning of the 18th century.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folios 1r, 316v: a note of ownership of the Karaite synagogue of <name type="place">Jerusalem</name>.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Daniel ben Mosheh ha-Melamed</name>: inscribed, folio 1r.</p>
							<p>A note stating that certain Avraham Rofe used the manuscript in 5476 (1716): inscribed, folio 1r.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM in-house.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Samuel ha-Rofe. Sefer Mitsvoth. Vol. I. Arabic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2405.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
